{{Quote|Count Dooku seeks a new ally with the power to defeat the Jedi. On the planet Rattatak, he encounters a mysterious fighter who dominates every opponent in the combat ring. She introduces herself to him as Asajj Ventress, a Sith warrior.|StarWars.com summary|<ref name="SW.com">{{SWArchive|url=clonewars/microseries/chapter/6.html|text=''Clone Wars'': Chapter Six (small)}}</ref>}}
"'''Chapter 6'''" is the sixth episode of the ''[[Star Wars: Clone Wars]]'' animated television series, and the sixth episode in [[Clone Wars: Season One|Season One]] and [[Star Wars: Clone Wars Volume One|Volume One]]. Directed by [[Genndy Tartakovsky]], the episode originally aired on [[Cartoon Network]] on [[November 14]], [[2003]].

==Plot summary==
{{Quote|The Dark Side is strong in me, for I am Sith.|Asajj Ventress to Count Dooku|<ref name="Episode">{{CW|6}}</ref>}}
[[File:RattatakWrestlemania-CW6.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Dooku and his guide watch as the gladiatorial battles rage below.]]
[[Count/Legends|Count]] [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]] journeys to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Rattatak/Legends|Rattatak]] to observe the planet's [[Gladiator/Legends|gladiatorial]] matches, in the hopes of finding a worthy successor to [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]]. Upon arrival, he is met by [[Unidentified henchman (the Cauldron)|his henchman]] and escorted into "[[The Cauldron]]," a large gladiatorial ring, and given a seat of honor.

Soon after Dooku sat down, the guide seated beside him is deftly replaced by a [[Asajj Ventress/Legends|cloaked figure]]. Without turning, Dooku praises the stealthiness of the substitution, claiming his guide would be impressed if he had not just been [[Death/Legends|killed]]. However, Dooku also states that he's not looking for a [[Spy/Legends|spy]].

With that, the figure bursts into the arena and easily takes out all of the gladiators (namely [[Blorga]], [[Grunda Dolma]], [[Nilo (Rodisar)|Nilo]], [[L8-L9]], [[Flalios]], [[Jasper McKnives]], [[Krutch]], [[Anchor Blue]], [[Swyy'm-Ee]] and [[Giant Flog]]), making deft use of [[Force jump/Legends|Force Jump]], [[Force speed/Legends|Force speed]] and other [[Force power/Legends|powers]]. Dooku stands, applauding and complimenting her, and inquiring where she learned such capabilities. The figure replies that they came easily to her&mdash;since she is a [[Sith/Legends|Sith]].

